OL,3,CHow Indian sarees are being celebrated
OL,4,Cby a group of women in Reading
OL,6,FThey are often made from raw silk or
OL,7,Fpure cotton - and can take a weaver a
OL,8,Fcouple of months to make just one.
OL,10,FThe materials used and even the way in
OL,11,Fwhich it is draped can often reflect
OL,12,Fdifferent regions in India, for
OL,13,Fexample, Mysore silk sarees are often
OL,14,Fworn in Karnataka.
OL,16,FShruthi Belgavi from Desiyard UK said:
OL,17,F"I thought why don't I bring this
OL,18,Fbeautiful collection to the UK, to
OL,19,Fcustomers here, where we can also
OL,20,Fsupport the weavers back home.
